\begin_layout Standard
This note aims to illustrate the properties of the most recent version of
 MAKRO to a series of shocks.
 The model is documented in several companion documents, see e.g.
 XXX.
 Before analyzing the impact of specific shocks, we discuss general properties
 of the transmission mechanisms present in the model.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
First, we describe the general response to demand shocks (Section 1.1), followed
 by similar considerations for supply shocks (Section 1.2 for labor supply
 and productivity, section 1.3 for shocks to foreign prices, and Section
 1.4 for financial shocks).
 After this, we discuss how public expenditure financing affects the model's
 dynamic responses (Section 1.5).
 Finally, we write briefly about the sectors in MAKRO.
 Given their significant contribution to GDP it is often enough to look
 at the service and manufacturing sectors if one wants to understand the
 marginal properties of the model (Section 1.6).
 The individual shock analyses are described in the subsequent sections.
